Panderichthys evidently was a ‘front-wheel drive’ animal that was incapable of tetrapod-like, hindlimb-propelled locomotion: the pelvic fin is much smaller than the pectoral fin; the pelvic girdle is not weight-bearing; the acetabulum is posteriorly oriented, rendering the tetrapod power-stroke impossible; and knee and elbow flexion would have been very limited.:
